    "## Part 1: Understanding Raster Subsetting\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.1 What is Raster Subsetting?\n",
    "\n",
    "Raster subsetting involves extracting a portion of a larger raster dataset based on:\n",
    "- **Geographic bounds** - Rectangular areas defined by coordinates\n",
    "- **Vector geometries** - Irregular shapes from shapefiles or polygons\n",
    "- **Pixel indices** - Specific rows and columns in the raster grid\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.2 Common Subsetting Scenarios\n",
    "\n",
    "**By Geographic Bounds:**\n",
    "- Extract elevation data for a watershed\n",
    "- Clip satellite imagery to a city boundary\n",
    "- Create regional climate datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "**By Vector Geometry:**\n",
    "- Mask raster data to administrative boundaries\n",
    "- Extract values within protected areas\n",
    "- Analyze data within custom study polygons"
   ]
  },
