    "### 1.3 Understanding Geographic Bounds\n",
    "\n",
    "Geographic bounds define a rectangular area using four coordinates:\n",
    "- **left (west)**: Minimum X coordinate\n",
    "- **bottom (south)**: Minimum Y coordinate  \n",
    "- **right (east)**: Maximum X coordinate\n",
    "- **top (north)**: Maximum Y coordinate\n",
    "\n",
    "**Important:** The order is `(left, bottom, right, top)` - this matches the order used in many GIS libraries."
